@angular/core.title: ElementRef
@angular/core.secure: Permitting direct access to the DOM can make your application more vulnerable to XSS attacks. Carefully review any use of `ElementRef` in your code. For more detail, see the [Security Guide](http://g.co/ng/security).

@angular/platform-browser.title: DomSanitizer
@angular/platform-browser.secure: Calling any of the `bypassSecurityTrust...` APIs disables Angular's built-in sanitization for the value passed in. Carefully check and audit all values and code paths going into this call. Make sure any user data is appropriately escaped for this security context. For more detail, see the [Security Guide](http://g.co/ng/security).
